Roman Hagara (b 30 April 1966 in Vienna) is an Austrian sailor in the Tornado class. Hagara, and his colleague Hans-Peter Steinacher won the Gold medal in the Tornado class at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, and successfully defended their title at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens. Hagara was the Flagbearer for the Austrian team at the 2004 Summer Olympics Opening Ceremony. 
